President Biden delivered a speech at Onondaga Community College in Syracuse, New York, celebrating the investment of $100 billion by Micron to build American factories and produce semiconductors. The investment is the largest of its kind in American history and will create nine thousand jobs. The President emphasized the importance of manufacturing in America and the need to bring back jobs that were lost to overseas outsourcing. He also highlighted his administration's efforts to lower prescription drug prices, invest in infrastructure, and reduce the deficit. The President criticized Republican plans to cut social security and Medicare and warned of the consequences of a government shutdown over these issues. He expressed optimism about America's future and praised the younger generation for their education, engagement, and lack of self-interest. The President concluded by emphasizing the strength and resilience of the United States.